HEADWORD: Crosstrees
<hw>Cross"trees`</hw> <pr>(-tr?z`)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>Pieces of timber at a masthead, to which are
attached the upper shrouds. At the head of lower masts in large vessels,
they support a semicircular platform called the
⟦ldquo⟧top.⟦rdquo⟧</def>⟦br⟧
